/Question : A Product Owner wants advice from the Scrum Master about estimating work in Scrum. What guidance should a Scrum Master give ? (Choose the best answer) 
/A) Estimates must be in relative units 
/B) Estimates are made by the Product Owner, but are best checked with the developers 
/C) Estimates are made by the people doing the work 
/D) Product Backlog items must be estimated in story points 
/E) Scrum forbids estimating 

C